{{- define "content" }}

Generate high-quality unit tests for the provided code.

Requirements:
- Use idiomatic Go
- Use table-driven tests (single test function with test cases) whenever possible
- Use the standard "testing" package only
- Keep tests deterministic and readable
- Do not include explanations, only code

Coverage expectations:
- Happy path
- Edge cases
- Error handling (if applicable)
- Boundary conditions

Guidelines:
- If the function is pure, write direct input/output tests
- If the function returns errors, include failure scenarios
- If dependencies exist, mock or stub them minimally
- Avoid flaky tests (no time.Now, randomness, external systems)

Structure:
- Prefer a single TestXxx function per target
- Use a slice of test cases (table-driven style)
- Each test case must include name, inputs, expected outputs

